        public void setEmptyChild​(int index)
        Set a new child at the index. This will reference a new object at index, with EPSILON. The child will not be epsilon, but a child pointing to epsilon. This is implemented like this to follow the concept of the grammar, that make a variable point to epsilon.

        index -
